swimming is great and, no, it won't turn you into a mouth breather. If you are thin and tall, you will likely have some potential...longer objects are faster in water. If you are short and fat, it will just be good cardio/general exercise. May make you super tired at first..maybe for the first year, so I would recommend swimming in the afternoon/evening if that's the case
